00:21:01,405 --> 00:21:06,035
It's like an open plaza.
A bunch of kids are playing.

277
00:21:06,495 --> 00:21:08,705
Okay, stay there.
I'm coming to you.

278
00:21:09,085 --> 00:21:10,085
Alright.

279
00:21:23,545 --> 00:21:25,705
Sir, can I get a quick interview?

280
00:21:28,595 --> 00:21:31,865
Sorry. I'm just waiting
for my grandson.

281
00:21:33,965 --> 00:21:37,185
Please, sir. I'll be quick.
I promise.

282
00:21:43,615 --> 00:21:45,815
Fine, just a sec then.

283
00:21:46,625 --> 00:21:47,625
Okay.

284
00:21:47,825 --> 00:21:49,464
I'll play you a dance clip.

285
00:21:49,465 --> 00:21:52,065
If you get the moves right,
that's 1,000 baht, yours to keep.

286
00:21:52,505 --> 00:21:54,865
Hmm? I can't dance.

287
00:21:55,105 --> 00:21:57,345
Alright then. How old are you?

288
00:21:58,545 --> 00:21:59,545
Seventy-five.

289
00:22:00,135 --> 00:22:02,695
Then 75 times that, all yours.

290
00:22:03,375 --> 00:22:08,305
Oh-ho. It's a lot of money.
You're giving it for free?

291
00:22:08,705 --> 00:22:10,595
I don't want it. Not dancing.

292
00:22:10,625 --> 00:22:11,855
It's not for free.

293
00:22:11,885 --> 00:22:12,545
Yeah?

294
00:22:12,595 --> 00:22:14,855
You just dance along
for everyone to watch.

295
00:22:15,095 --> 00:22:16,735
I told you, I can't dance.

296
00:22:16,935 --> 00:22:18,385
No need to be shy, sir.

297
00:22:18,875 --> 00:22:19,875
Hit it.

298
00:22:32,465 --> 00:22:33,685
Okay, that's enough.

299
00:22:33,975 --> 00:22:36,435
I'm going to find my grandson.

300
00:22:37,085 --> 00:22:39,865
Yo, guys, some noise for Grandpa.

301
00:22:39,895 --> 00:22:40,705
Dance.

302
00:22:40,725 --> 00:22:42,185
- Yo.
- Dance, dance.

303
00:22:43,585 --> 00:22:44,875
- Dance, Grandpa.
- Dance.

304
00:22:44,895 --> 00:22:47,465
You've gotta dance now. Watch me.

305
00:22:47,485 --> 00:22:49,485
- Dance, dance.
- Dance, dance.

306
00:22:49,735 --> 00:22:52,025
- Woo...
- Woo...

307
00:22:52,325 --> 00:22:53,705
Come on, sir. Just dance.

308
00:22:56,045 --> 00:22:57,785
Hey, stop, stop.

309
00:23:02,145 --> 00:23:03,225
Are you alright?

310
00:23:11,895 --> 00:23:13,865
It's for fun, lighten up.

311
00:23:14,335 --> 00:23:16,945
Fun how?
He didn't want to be filmed?

312
00:23:18,425 --> 00:23:21,465
Do not post it.
You know what PDPA is, right?

313
00:23:39,375 --> 00:23:40,375
Come sit here.

314
00:23:40,865 --> 00:23:42,145
- Hmm?
- This way.

315
00:23:51,605 --> 00:23:53,345
Are you okay?

316
00:23:54,485 --> 00:23:55,485
I'm fine.

317
00:23:56,555 --> 00:23:59,465
Next time, you can just walk away.

318
00:24:00,905 --> 00:24:03,585
Hmm. I just couldn't
find the opening.

319
00:24:04,905 --> 00:24:06,265
Don't worry about them.

320
00:24:06,705 --> 00:24:09,035
Mostly, all they want
is view counts.

321
00:24:09,595 --> 00:24:11,225
They don't care about privacy.

322
00:24:12,265 --> 00:24:14,505
I don't even know
why I had to dance.

323
00:24:18,425 --> 00:24:21,615
Okay... I'll walk slower.

324
00:24:23,055 --> 00:24:24,175
So you won't lose me again.

325
00:24:25,905 --> 00:24:26,905
Forget it.

326
00:24:29,145 --> 00:24:31,025
I really don't belong here.

327
00:24:32,385 --> 00:24:33,615
That's not true.

328
00:24:34,015 --> 00:24:38,085
Just because you don't play along
doesn't mean you don't fit in here.

329
00:24:39,345 --> 00:24:41,345
You just open up
to the right things.

330
00:24:42,065 --> 00:24:43,225
You'll be fine.

331
00:24:51,755 --> 00:24:52,785
So...

332
00:24:54,085 --> 00:24:55,225
let's just head home.

333
00:24:58,005 --> 00:24:59,985
Wait. I need to make a quick call.

334
00:25:11,025 --> 00:25:12,145
"Save."

335
00:25:14,755 --> 00:25:15,755
Where are you?

336
00:25:16,035 --> 00:25:17,035
I have to head back.

337
00:25:17,255 --> 00:25:18,265
Is everything okay?

338
00:25:18,825 --> 00:25:22,025
Yeah, I just remembered
I have to do something.

339
00:25:22,585 --> 00:25:23,625
See you at school.

340
00:25:25,285 --> 00:25:26,285
Save.

341
00:25:33,775 --> 00:25:34,775
Let's go.

342
00:25:42,355 --> 00:25:43,355
Easy, Grandpa.

343
00:25:50,385 --> 00:25:53,055
Excuse me, can I get
a quick interview for some content?

344
00:25:53,955 --> 00:25:56,545
Sorry. We can't.

345
00:26:01,185 --> 00:26:02,305
Oh, thank you.

346
00:26:06,095 --> 00:26:10,185
Just because you don't play along
doesn't mean you don't fit in here.

347
00:26:10,335 --> 00:26:12,405
You just open up
to the right things.

348
00:26:12,505 --> 00:26:13,505
You'll be fine.

349
00:26:13,825 --> 00:26:14,825
Hold on.

350
00:26:22,325 --> 00:26:23,865
What kind of content?

351
00:26:25,115 --> 00:26:26,225
- Oh...
- Hehe.

352
00:26:36,315 --> 00:26:41,505
Some new trends like kids' names.

353
00:26:41,795 --> 00:26:42,985
Turbo.

354
00:26:43,915 --> 00:26:46,505
Nam Nile.

355
00:26:47,905 --> 00:26:50,505
A guy in a skirt. Aw.

356
00:26:58,025 --> 00:27:01,385
"Turbo slung his navy backpack
over one shoulder,"

357
00:27:02,055 --> 00:27:06,855
"and made straight
for the meeting spot."

358
00:27:07,325 --> 00:27:10,065
"Dead center of Siam Square,"

359
00:27:10,745 --> 00:27:14,505
"a concrete jungle
stripped of every tree."

360
00:27:15,655 --> 00:27:20,185
"The air was thick with heat
baking off the pavement."

361
00:27:20,545 --> 00:27:24,795
"People moved fast,
like hunters on a trail."

362
00:27:26,025 --> 00:27:28,905
"And there stood Nam Nile,
waiting."

363
00:27:29,785 --> 00:27:33,265
"His scent drifted over,
soft and faint,"

364
00:27:33,845 --> 00:27:35,865
"like a bloom
luring something in."

365
00:27:37,305 --> 00:27:38,305
Come in.

366
00:27:42,905 --> 00:27:44,325
How are you doing?

367
00:27:44,345 --> 00:27:45,965
Got a lot written down?

368
00:27:46,275 --> 00:27:47,275
Yeah.

369
00:27:49,065 --> 00:27:50,785
I owe you a lot for this.

370
00:27:51,045 --> 00:27:52,045
Save.

371
00:27:53,225 --> 00:27:54,665
I want to ask you something.

372
00:27:55,275 --> 00:27:56,275
Yeah?

373
00:27:57,905 --> 00:28:00,985
When your guy held your hand...

374
00:28:01,665 --> 00:28:02,705
how did it feel?

375
00:28:10,825 --> 00:28:12,295
It was... strange, Grandpa.

376
00:28:12,315 --> 00:28:13,315
Hmm?

377
00:28:13,345 --> 00:28:14,984
Besides Dad and you,

378
00:28:14,985 --> 00:28:17,225
I've never been looked after
by another guy before.

379
00:28:17,965 --> 00:28:19,345
Did it feel good?

380
00:28:20,265 --> 00:28:21,265
Why do you ask?

381
00:28:21,345 --> 00:28:23,344
Well, I'm writing a novel.

382
00:28:23,345 --> 00:28:26,585
I need to understand
what the characters feel, deep down.

383
00:28:27,565 --> 00:28:30,025
So did you like it
when he held your hand?

384
00:28:30,825 --> 00:28:33,905
Why ask me? Use your imagination.

385
00:28:34,095 --> 00:28:35,095
Ah?

386
00:28:35,605 --> 00:28:39,145
You're here now
with firsthand experience.

387
00:28:39,335 --> 00:28:41,715
Why would I bother imagining?

388
00:28:41,745 --> 00:28:42,815
So?

389
00:28:44,075 --> 00:28:45,075
Um.

390
00:28:47,265 --> 00:28:48,265
Shy?

391
00:28:48,785 --> 00:28:50,625
Silly question? I'm going to bed.

392
00:28:50,645 --> 00:28:51,645
Hmm?

393
00:28:54,565 --> 00:28:55,565
Save.

394
00:28:57,215 --> 00:28:59,935
Hey, Save.

395
00:29:00,945 --> 00:29:02,185
What now?

396
00:29:02,745 --> 00:29:06,825
What you did today
was for my novel, wasn't it?

397
00:29:07,835 --> 00:29:08,835
Huh.

398
00:29:08,865 --> 00:29:09,945
Okay.

399
00:29:09,975 --> 00:29:11,155
What's the question again?

400
00:29:12,315 --> 00:29:14,585
When he held your hand,
did your heart race?

401
00:29:14,865 --> 00:29:15,785
Grandpa.

402
00:29:15,786 --> 00:29:17,105
Think about it.

403
00:29:36,485 --> 00:29:39,184
It didn't... race exactly.

404
00:29:39,185 --> 00:29:40,145
Oh?

405
00:29:40,146 --> 00:29:41,665
It was more like a jolt.

406
00:29:42,745 --> 00:29:43,895
Think about it.

407
00:29:44,145 --> 00:29:46,705
A guy who isn't my dad
grabbed my hand to cross the street.

408
00:29:47,625 --> 00:29:48,625
The feeling was...

409
00:29:51,695 --> 00:29:52,705
hard to put into words.

410
00:29:53,205 --> 00:29:54,245
Figure it out yourself.

411
00:29:55,505 --> 00:29:57,425
So that's what
the first step feels like.

412
00:29:59,775 --> 00:30:00,835
Satisfied now?

413
00:30:00,865 --> 00:30:02,785
Very. Thank you.

414
00:30:06,195 --> 00:30:07,195
Huh.

415
00:30:15,065 --> 00:30:16,385
Here we go.

416
00:30:17,445 --> 00:30:18,505
Okay, everyone line up.

417
00:30:18,915 --> 00:30:22,865
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8,

418
00:30:23,465 --> 00:30:26,105
9, 10, 11, 12, 13.

419
00:30:28,895 --> 00:30:29,895
Who's missing?

420
00:30:30,105 --> 00:30:31,105
Who?

421
00:30:31,865 --> 00:30:32,865
Hmm?

422
00:30:33,575 --> 00:30:35,185
- Did he miscount?
- Who is it?

423
00:30:35,545 --> 00:30:36,625
- Dad.
- What?

424
00:30:36,655 --> 00:30:37,675
Someone's missing.

425
00:30:37,705 --> 00:30:38,585
What?

426
00:30:38,585 --> 00:30:39,475
Who's gone?

427
00:30:39,495 --> 00:30:40,585
Phi Save.

428
00:30:41,785 --> 00:30:42,945
Jingjai's missing.

429
00:30:46,135 --> 00:30:46,935
Jingjai.

430
00:30:46,955 --> 00:30:54,265
- Jingjai, Jingjai.
- Jingjai.

431
00:30:54,755 --> 00:30:57,305
- Jingjai, where are you?
- Jingjai.

432
00:30:59,385 --> 00:31:02,105
There. The ghost child crying sound.

433
00:31:12,065 --> 00:31:13,145
Jingjai, where are you?

434
00:31:21,865 --> 00:31:22,865
Jingjai.

435
00:31:30,455 --> 00:31:32,815
Jingjai, why are you here?

436
00:31:37,765 --> 00:31:39,705
I don't want to go to school.

437
00:32:11,985 --> 00:32:14,345
Ghost? It's just Jingjai.

438
00:32:16,655 --> 00:32:18,185
How foolish of you, Jedi.

439
00:32:18,395 --> 00:32:21,145
Saw her from behind.
Thought it was a ghost.

440
00:32:30,085 --> 00:32:32,745
I miss Mom. I want to go home.

441
00:32:35,075 --> 00:32:39,145
Oh, Jingjai.
Your mom's not here anymore.

442
00:32:39,425 --> 00:32:41,465
She went to work in Lampang.

443
00:32:42,225 --> 00:32:44,105
I want to see Mom.

444
00:32:45,545 --> 00:32:47,945
When she's done working,
she'll come to visit.

445
00:32:48,225 --> 00:32:52,825
For now, you can do something
or play with your friends.

446
00:32:53,165 --> 00:32:54,165
How about that?

447
00:32:54,685 --> 00:32:57,945
Well, tell me about your friends.
How are they?

448
00:32:58,995 --> 00:32:59,995
Hmm?

449
00:33:02,025 --> 00:33:05,345
She doesn't really talk to anyone.
She mostly keeps to herself.

450
00:33:07,725 --> 00:33:10,705
Jingjai, you're going to
be here a while.

451
00:33:11,025 --> 00:33:13,785
You need to open up
and play with the other kids.

452
00:33:16,425 --> 00:33:19,045
And you still have to
go to school.

453
00:33:19,705 --> 00:33:22,185
When you get back,
I'll let you call Mom.

454
00:33:22,525 --> 00:33:24,305
Can I call her now?

455
00:33:24,545 --> 00:33:27,865
Afraid not. She's at work.

456
00:33:29,705 --> 00:33:32,505
I'll just wait till she's back.

457
00:33:42,115 --> 00:33:45,025
Jingjai, come to school with us.

458
00:33:46,225 --> 00:33:48,425
Yeah, school is fun.

459
00:33:48,845 --> 00:33:50,745
We'll do a lot of fun things.

460
00:33:54,105 --> 00:33:55,105
Like what?

461
00:34:06,465 --> 00:34:07,505
Go ahead.

462
00:34:11,425 --> 00:34:13,465
Alright, everyone's here.

463
00:34:13,745 --> 00:34:14,905
- Hmph.
- Hmm.

464
00:34:21,875 --> 00:34:22,905
Huh.

465
00:34:25,885 --> 00:34:27,035
Take a look at this.

466
00:34:27,065 --> 00:34:29,315
"Be Hard on Me, President."

467
00:34:50,915 --> 00:34:54,345
"Auntie Mart's Sanae Chan."

468
00:34:59,355 --> 00:35:03,705
Hello everyone,
presenting Sanae Chan desserts.

469
00:35:03,915 --> 00:35:07,144
Recipe passed down from grandma,
with a twist from the grandkids.

470
00:35:07,145 --> 00:35:12,105
One of a kind,
one with lots of love.

471
00:35:12,935 --> 00:35:16,545
So smash that cart.
Keep tapping, non-stop.

472
00:35:16,965 --> 00:35:20,864
Sixty baht a box. Buy three
and get free shipping nationwide.

473
00:35:20,865 --> 00:35:24,505
Wow...

474
00:35:24,915 --> 00:35:26,781
- "Lovely. Hard to find item."
- Oh, Phi Sorn, a comment.

475
00:35:26,805 --> 00:35:30,265
Thank you for that one viewer.

476
00:35:32,425 --> 00:35:37,985
This is a royal-style Sanae Chan
with a Japanese fusion twist.

477
00:35:38,265 --> 00:35:40,105
So delicious.

478
00:35:40,585 --> 00:35:42,225
Go ahead and add to cart.

479
00:35:42,245 --> 00:35:45,655
We'd love for you to try.
It's really that good.

480
00:35:53,465 --> 00:35:54,865
The viewer's gone.

481
00:35:54,895 --> 00:35:56,795
Hmm? Really?

482
00:35:58,175 --> 00:36:01,115
Mart, maybe I'll get to
the delivery app for now.

483
00:36:01,715 --> 00:36:03,105
Can you handle the live solo?

484
00:36:09,915 --> 00:36:13,075
Hey, why cut it off?
It's been only two hours.

485
00:36:13,205 --> 00:36:17,665
Right, two hours.
There's no sign of anybody now.

486
00:36:19,495 --> 00:36:22,305
How about I do a cartwheel
when selling it?

487
00:36:22,905 --> 00:36:28,305
Oh, no. You could hurt yourself,
old man.

488
00:36:28,765 --> 00:36:32,545
"Wow. This is way too sweet."

489
00:36:32,575 --> 00:36:34,725
"Someone give them
a proper BL series?"

490
00:36:34,885 --> 00:36:36,745
"BL done absolutely right."

491
00:36:40,425 --> 00:36:41,545
- Phi Sorn.
- Hmm?

492
00:36:41,725 --> 00:36:42,925
Is this our boy?

493
00:36:47,745 --> 00:36:48,825
- Save?
- Save?

494
00:36:51,885 --> 00:36:52,905
Hey.

495
00:36:53,625 --> 00:36:55,305
That's Save and Guy.

496
00:37:02,025 --> 00:37:04,545
Yo, why are you holding hands?

497
00:37:05,025 --> 00:37:09,105
Okay, are you two secretly
together or what?

498
00:37:11,065 --> 00:37:13,135
Ugh... we're not. Together how?

499
00:37:13,505 --> 00:37:16,425
People just ship us. Right, Guy?

500
00:37:18,305 --> 00:37:19,345
Tell them.

501
00:37:20,765 --> 00:37:23,825
Yeah, he was walking slow,
so I pulled him along.

502
00:37:24,225 --> 00:37:28,225
Yeah, right. Is that true?

503
00:37:29,265 --> 00:37:30,265
It is true.

504
00:37:30,325 --> 00:37:32,965
Hey, bunch of comments.
You're famous now.

505
00:37:33,965 --> 00:37:34,745
Let me see.

506
00:37:34,746 --> 00:37:36,305
Wow, so many.

507
00:37:36,745 --> 00:37:38,085
- Yeah, see?
- Yeah.

508
00:37:38,225 --> 00:37:39,365
Our friends have blown up.

509
00:37:41,625 --> 00:37:44,905
Hey, sorry I had to keep it
from everyone for now.

510
00:37:45,865 --> 00:37:46,985
You get it, right?

511
00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:48,345
Yeah, I get it.

512
00:37:50,855 --> 00:37:51,855
Thanks, man.

513
00:37:55,265 --> 00:37:56,265
Tell me something.

514
00:37:56,825 --> 00:37:58,745
That day we went out, were you okay?

515
00:37:59,385 --> 00:38:00,545
You left suddenly.

516
00:38:04,025 --> 00:38:05,505
Yeah, I was fine.

517
00:38:06,785 --> 00:38:08,905
I... really had something to do.

518
00:38:09,805 --> 00:38:10,905
Don't overthink it.

519
00:38:11,505 --> 00:38:14,225
How can I not?
You just disappeared on me.

520
00:38:15,625 --> 00:38:16,625
It was...

521
00:38:17,625 --> 00:38:18,945
my first time.

522
00:38:20,365 --> 00:38:21,965
I felt a little off.

523
00:38:23,585 --> 00:38:25,385
Just... give me some time.

524
00:38:26,745 --> 00:38:29,665
Sure. So that means
we'll have to go out more often.

525
00:38:30,065 --> 00:38:31,065
You'll get used to it.

526
00:38:33,055 --> 00:38:34,055
Mm-hmm.

527
00:39:17,865 --> 00:39:20,124
Hello, sweetheart, you're back.

528
00:39:20,125 --> 00:39:24,874
Now, now. Go wash up.
Then come down for dinner.

529
00:39:24,875 --> 00:39:26,784
All your favorites tonight.

530
00:39:26,785 --> 00:39:28,225
What's going on with you two?

531
00:39:28,855 --> 00:39:31,345
Acting like a pack of
pampering softies.

532
00:39:31,855 --> 00:39:34,465
Um, we'd just... like to talk to you.

533
00:39:34,705 --> 00:39:36,265
Eat first, then we'll talk.

534
00:39:36,285 --> 00:39:37,985
Whatever it is, just say it now.

535
00:39:44,105 --> 00:39:45,225
So, Mom, what's it about?

536
00:39:46,165 --> 00:39:48,345
Hey, I have no parts in this.

537
00:39:48,955 --> 00:39:51,185
They roped me here.

538
00:39:57,225 --> 00:39:59,144
We're family.

539
00:39:59,145 --> 00:40:01,545
We talk about anything, right?

540
00:40:02,205 --> 00:40:03,224
Right, Phi Sorn?

541
00:40:03,225 --> 00:40:04,225
Mm-hmm.

542
00:40:04,725 --> 00:40:07,745
You've always been a good kid.

543
00:40:07,775 --> 00:40:09,825
Whatever you are, whoever you like,

544
